text: Chionodes occlusa is a moth in the family Gelechiidae. It is found in North America, where it has been recorded from New York, the Northwest Territories, from Ontario to British Columbia and south to Arizona and California.Chionodes at funetmothphotographersgroup ==References== Category:Chionodes Category:Moths described in 1916 Category:Moths of North America
title: Chionodes occlusa
